= Subscript and Superscript

Subscript and superscript text for mathematical and scientific notation.

== Basic Subscript

This paragraph contains H~2~O (water).

Chemical formula: C~6~H~12~O~6~ (glucose).

== Basic Superscript

This paragraph contains E=mc^2^ (Einstein's equation).

Mathematical expression: x^2^ + y^2^ = z^2^.

== Subscript Examples

Water molecule: H~2~O

Carbon dioxide: CO~2~

Glucose: C~6~H~12~O~6~

== Superscript Examples

Square: x^2^

Cube: x^3^

Power of ten: 10^6^

== Combined Subscript and Superscript

Mathematical expression: x~i~^2^ + y~j~^2^.

== Subscript and Superscript with Other Formatting

This paragraph has H~2~O and *bold* text.

This paragraph has E=mc^2^ and _italic_ text.

